# Base Environment Configuration
# ================================
# Values in this file are shared across ALL environments (dev, prod, test).
# They are loaded first, then overridden by .env.{mode} and .env.local.
#
# Priority (highest wins):
#   1. .env.local          (gitignored — personal overrides)
#   2. .env.{mode}         (mode-specific: .env.development, .env.production)
#   3. .env                (this file — shared defaults)
#
# Use the admin CLI to manage shared values:
#   npx tsx scripts/admin-cli.ts config set-super-admin admin@example.com --shared --yes
#
# Common shared values:
#   SUPER_ADMIN_EMAIL, GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, etc.
